race.comment: FIRST EMPIRE (8) was edged out first-up at Doomben then started favourite in Saturday grade here last start and was beaten under a length over 1200m, making a late charge but running out of ground. Scored third-up last prep over 1350m at Ipswich. Hasn't raced for 30 days but back in midweek company he looks the goods. DIVA LAS VEGAS (12) transferred to Michael Freedman this prep and has raced well without winning in NSW provincials. Found the line well over 1300m at Kembla last time so a first go at 1400m looks timely. HE'S FOR THE GIRLS (4) has been freshened up since finishing midfield in a strong form race over 1200m at the Sunshine Coast a month ago. The track was soft that day which he doesn't enjoy. Needs this sort of trip now so watch for a better run. POUTCHEK (13) returned with an eye-catcher at massive odds recently at Doomben. Is a winner here at the trip so keep her in mind. RETAINER (11) went well last start when attempting this trip for the first time. Worth following.
